{
  "texts": [
    "We found that GPT-4V was the only model that showed a relation to human judgements, with a regression coefficient of 1.15 (95% credible interval (95% CI) 1.04, 1.27) and an R 2 value of 0.066.",
    "However, the regression coefficient between individual humans and the mean over humans was still larger, with a coefficient of 1.46 (95% CI 1.41, 1.52) and an R 2 value of 0.354.",
    "To test the models' causal reasoning capabilities, we used synthetic images from refs.",
    "100,101, which depicted block towers that were stable but might collapse if one of the blocks was removed (see Supplementary Fig. 2 for an example).",
    "We started by asking the models to count the blocks in the image."
  ]
}